  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "That a great part Of the initial\nexpense of constructing the Spo-\nkane Falls & Northern railway was\ncontributed by the people of Spo-\nkane and eastern Washington.\nThat the territory between the\nNorthern Pacific railway tracks and\nPine and Browne streets used to\nbe known as \"Shantytown\" and was\nalmost covered by the cabins of\nsquatters?\n\n\nThat Gonzaga college was found\ned in 1887?\n\n\nThat the first white child born\nin Spokane was Cazenova Cowley, a\nsister of Arthur Cowley, the archi-\ntect?\n\n\nThat edible frogs were once nu-\nmerous and easily caught in a pool\nof stagnant water near the old\nFranklin school?"
    }
